SIMPLE: whitewood
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Whitewood
<hw>White"wood`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The soft and
easily-worked wood of the tulip tree (<spn>Liriodendron
tulipifera</spn>). It is much used in cabinetwork, carriage building,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Several other kinds of light-colored wood are called
<xex>whitewood</xex> in various countries, as the wood of <spn>Bignonia
leucoxylon</spn> in the West Indies, of <spn>Pittosporum bicolor</spn>
in Tasmania, etc.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Whitewood bark</b></col>. <cd>See the Note under
<er>Canella</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whitewort</ent>⟦br⟧
